10:
Yeah, I'm okay... mostly. Man, that 
stings!
13:
It wouldn't do to push yourself.
Let's head home and bandage you up.
17:
Oh, it sounds like you could use the 
Stars' blessing!
21:
Huh? The what?
Who are you, exactly?
26:
My name is Liesel.
I must be going, but may the Stars 
above bless you with their Light. 
Farewell!
31:
Uh, thanks? 
...Wait, the cut is gone! She healed me!
35:
Some sort of priestess or cleric, by the 
looks of it.
Either way, it isn't safe to wander 
through the Kaleidoscope alone!
39:
Yeah, she shouldn't be here without 
a buddy! Let's hurry!
43:
There she is!
...Wait, who are those guys? Is that her 
party?
46:
Awfully dangerous to be out here on 
your lonesome, ain't it?
47:
The Kaleidoscope's a lonely place—no 
one'd hear you callin' for help if 
somethin' were to... happen.
50:
Oh, I'll be quite all right, thank you!
Do you gentlemen need anything? 
I can heal your party, if you'd like.
52:
Y'know what I could really go for 
right now? ...YOUR WALLET!
Give us all you've got, 
or you'll regret it!
64:
She knocked them all out, then... 
healed them all? Wait, why?!
67:
Though you cannot always see the 
Stars, the Stars can always see you—
even in the Kaleidoscope's darkest 
depths.
69:
You must take care not to stray from 
their teachings.
75:
You did a very naughty thing, but the 
Stars in all their benevolence are 
giving you another chance. I pray 
you'll never lose sight of their Light 
again.
78:
Stars' benevolence, my ass!
Who the hell do you think you are?!
82:
Who do you think YOU are?! How DARE 
you try to rob the Angel of the 
Kaleidoscope!?
88:
Hah! You messed with the wrong 
fanclub! No one touches our Angel!
90:
Who are you two? If you're with those 
punks, you're in for a world of pain!
93:
Calm down, please, that won't be 
necessary. They were trying to help 
me.
96:
Oh, in that case, the Guardian Angels 
welcome you with open arms, 
brothers!
98:
Liesel, your party members are uh... 
pretty passionate, huh?
102:
Oh, I don't have a party myself, but I do 
believe I've met this man before.
I'm sorry—I'm afraid your name is 
escaping me.
105:
No, don't worry about that! I'm not 
worthy, anyways. I'm just happy you 
remembered me at all, Angel! I-I can't 
believe it!
107:
Oh yeah, you called her the Angel of 
the Kaleidoscope a minute ago. 
What's all that about?
110:
What? You mean you don't know? 
You've GOT to be joking! Half of 
Palpebra stans her!
112:
Stans? What's that mean?
...Whatever it is, it sounds like a pain.
114:
Rude! Liesel patrols the Kaleidoscope 
blessing us unworthy adventurers with 
her healing magic—all out of the 
goodness of her heart!
115:
There comes a point in any 
adventurer's career when you're cold, 
hurt, and alone, crying for your 
mommy!—and then the Stars send 
you Liesel! She's a true saint!
118:
Your mommy? Yes, I remember now! 
You must be Robbertson. I found you 
crying for your mommy after a bad 
run-in with a blobble.
121:
Squeeee! Stars above, she knows my 
name!
125:
Oh no! What's wrong? Don't you worry, 
I'll have you back on your feet right 
away!
129:
Nah, I think you can just leave him. 
Look at that smile...
133:
Hmm. While it's very noble of you to 
offer adventurers your services for 
free, how do you provide for yourself?
136: Oh, I get by just fine!
138:
Adventurers often bring me gifts of 
food, and I can sleep inside the church 
when it's cold or rainy!
144:
Wait, you mean you sleep outside 
otherwise?
...You don't have a home?
147:
It's quite nice, really, sleeping in the 
Stars' motherly embrace.
154:
We would be happy to offer you 
lodging in our village.
157:
I have nothing but respect for your 
charitable lifestyle, and yet... I worry for 
your health and safety.
160:
We've got plenty of empty rooms, so 
you don't need to worry about rent or 
anything. You're also welcome to join 
us for meals!
164: Oh, why, that's very kind of you!
168:
Thank you. Praise the stars for their 
Guidance—I've no doubt they led us to 
each other.
171:
Hey! Wait! Hold up, hooold up! That's 
against the Guardian Angel rules! 
Stans aren't allowed to ask about or 
interfere with Liesel's private life!
